;W[ns]LB[os:1][ps:2][ns:3]C[Dia. 03 Complex Counting Method

{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}

After the hane and connection on the first line, one side's territory will increase and the other side's territory will decrease.
That's why the counting is comlicated.

When only one side's territory has increased or decreased that is called \cf1\b simple counting method\cf0\b0 .

When both sides' territory have increased or decreased at the same time, that is called \cf1\b complex counting method\cf0\b0 .

In this diagram or in \b Dia. 02\b0 , Black 1 and 3 is a \cf2\b 2 points \cf1 gote endgame\cf0\b0  sequence.


